comments.body:
The problem log info is just telling you the name the problem log would have if it needed to generate one. We should hide that as a debug or trace message probably. If there's no problem log file in your local directory, you shouldn't have to worry about one.

Can you run this again with the {{-l trace}} option and report the details here? It looks like it's just stopping after the alloy compile, but perhaps the trace log will give us more info.
